## Implementation Details

The mention daemon has been successfully implemented with the following key features:

### Authentication
- Persists Twitter login session using a cookie file to avoid requiring login on every restart
- Cookie file is stored at `cookies/twitter-cookies.json` relative to the workspace
- Falls back to manual login if cookies are expired or invalid

### Mention Detection & Processing
- Polls Twitter for mentions of the configured TWITTER_USERNAME
- Extracts mention text, tweet URL, username, and tweet ID
- Maintains a queue of mentions to be processed
- Tracks processing status in `processed_mentions.json` (pending, success, failed)
- Retries mentions with "pending" or "failed" status on daemon restart

### Space URL Detection & Audio Extraction
- First attempts to extract Space URL from the mention text using regex pattern `https?:\/\/(?:twitter\.com|x\.com)\/i\/spaces\/[\w\d]+`
- If not found, navigates to the mention tweet and attempts to find it by scrolling up the thread:
  - Uses `page.goto(tweetUrl)` with `waitUntil: 'domcontentloaded'` to load the mention tweet
  - Iteratively scrolls up the page using `window.scrollBy(0, -window.innerHeight)` up to 10 attempts
  - After each scroll, waits for content to load with `page.waitForTimeout(1000)` and takes screenshots
  - Checks for Space content in visible tweets after each scroll using custom detection logic
- When a tweet with Space content is found (identified by "Play recording" button):
  - Identifies articles containing Space content using `article` elements with text matching "Play recording"
  - Finds the specific Play button using `getByRole('button', { name: 'Play recording' })` within the article
  - Uses `{ force: true }` with the click to bypass potential actionability issues
  - Sets up network interception before clicking using:
    ```typescript
    const m3u8PromiseResolvers: any = {};
    const m3u8Promise = new Promise((resolve, reject) => {
      m3u8PromiseResolvers.resolve = resolve;
      m3u8PromiseResolvers.reject = reject;
    });
    
    // Listen for all network requests containing .m3u8
    page.on('request', request => {
      const url = request.url();
      if (url.includes('.m3u8')) {
        logger.debug(`[ M3U8] Found potential M3U8 URL: ${url}`);
        m3u8PromiseResolvers.resolve(url);
      }
    });
    ```
  - Clicks the "Play recording" button and waits for the m3u8 request up to 30 seconds
  - Falls back to checking API responses if direct m3u8 request isn't detected:
    ```typescript
    page.on('response', async response => {
      const url = response.url();
      if (url.includes('/api/1.1/live_video_stream/status/')) {
        try {
          const responseJson = await response.json();
          // Extract m3u8 URL from the JSON response if present
          // ...
        } catch (e) {}
      }
    });
    ```

### Space Title Extraction
- Uses a multi-stage approach to extract the Space title:
  1. First attempt before clicking Play:
     - Checks for title within `div[data-testid="card.layoutLarge.media.title"]` or `span[data-testid="card.layoutSmall.media.title"]`
     - Looks for text directly within the article that matches known Space title patterns
  2. If no title found, clicks Play button and tries again:
     - Waits for player modal/popup with `page.waitForTimeout(2000)`
     - Looks for title in heading elements: `h1, h2[aria-level="2"], span[role="heading"]`
     - Specifically targets `h2[aria-level="2"]` which often contains the title after playback starts
     - Example: `const titleElement = page.locator('h2[aria-level="2"]').first();`
  3. Uses text content pattern matching as fallback:
     - Searches for text fragments matching Space naming conventions
     - Searches for capitalized phrases that could represent titles
- Handles failures with specific error handling:
  - Takes screenshots at each attempt for debugging
  - Logs detailed failures including which selectors were attempted
  - Throws a specific titled error (`[TITLE_EXTRACTION_FAILED]`) if extraction fails
  - Treats title extraction failure as a critical error for that specific job but allows daemon to continue

### Network Request Interception & Audio Extraction
- Uses Playwright's network interception to capture the m3u8 audio stream URL:
  ```typescript
  // Set up interception for .m3u8 files
  await page.route('**/*.m3u8*', route => {
    const url = route.request().url();
    logger.debug(`[ M3U8] Intercepted M3U8 request: ${url}`);
    capturedM3u8Url = url;
    route.continue(); // Allow the request to proceed
  });
  ```
- Once m3u8 URL is captured, uses FFmpeg to download the audio stream:
  ```typescript
  const outputPath = path.join(process.cwd(), 'downloads', `${spaceId}.mp3`);
  const ffmpegCommand = `ffmpeg -i "${m3u8Url}" -c copy -bsf:a aac_adtstoasc "${outputPath}"`;
  ```
- Handles various audio formats and quality levels in the m3u8 playlist
- Implements timeouts and retry logic for the audio download process
- Uploads the downloaded audio to S3 with proper metadata including Space ID and title

### Language Detection
- Analyzes mention text to detect requested target language 
- Uses a comprehensive mapping of language names, codes, and aliases
- Supports formats like "dub in english", "translate to spanish", or direct mentions of language names
- Defaults to English if no specific language is detected
- Extracts regional accent codes where applicable (e.g., es_la vs es_es)

### Concurrent Processing
- Browser tasks (navigation, clicking, posting replies) are performed sequentially
- Backend processing (download, upload, SpeechLab API calls) runs concurrently
- This architecture allows multiple long-running SpeechLab jobs to execute in parallel
- Uses separate queues for mention initiation and final replies

### User Communication
- Posts an immediate acknowledgment reply when a valid Space is found
- Posts a final reply with the translation link when processing completes
- Posts appropriate error messages if processing fails

### Error Handling & Recovery
- Gracefully handles failures at each step of the process
- Marks mentions with appropriate status in the persistent JSON file
- Screenshots key steps for debugging purposes in `debug-screenshots` directory